parameters: Umi "This has become such a hassle."
Kru "Is that what's-it-called cave really such a dangerous place?"
Umi "The cave is far. Umi hates getting tired."
Kru "Eh? You're not going? The chieftain will be angry, you know."
Umi "Let the chieftain be angry. Umi hates the chieftain."

Kru "No way, that's sad for the chieftain. He doesn't seem like such a bad
person."

Umi "The chieftain is a good person. He gives delicious things. Umi liked
the chieftain until yesterday. Starting today, Umi hates him."
Kru "Miss Umi, you're quite moody, aren't you?"

Umi "Mi-A... don't be so mad... I apologize for speaking ill of the
chieftain."
Umi "Sigh, understood. I'll go to the cave."
Kru "Eh! Mi-A said that? And you listen to Mi-A..."

Umi "Mi-A is Umi's family. Umi listens to what Mi-A says. Mi-A listens to
what Umi says."

Kru "I don't quite understand, but thank you. I must repay the favor of a
night's lodging and a meal."
Umi "Sigh. The southern exit of the village. From there, head west."
"呼種の洞窟に向かう。呼種の洞窟は村から出て西の方角"
Umi: "Haha, just kidding. You did well. Here, have some juice."
Kru: "Phew------!! A drink after a job well done is the best!!"
Kru: "What's up? What are you talking about?"
Umi: "You don't need to understand. Now then..."
Umi: "I'm going to prepare the meat... Just wait until dinner."
Umi: "Umi likes to eat. So I like to cook too."
Kru: "I see, it comes naturally then. I'm looking forward to it!"
Umi: "You can look forward to it. We got some good meat."
Kru: "Oh, well. We both worked hard on it. No big deal."
Kru: (Could it be... my heart's racing because she touched my chest...?)
Kru: (And... being thanked by Umi somehow makes me... happy...)

Umi: "Well then, Umi's busy. Why don't you go see the chieftain or
something?"
